I'm fairly new to the area and decided to treat myself and my partner. This place had good reviews and offered picked/delivery options. We've ordered twice so far and each time the food has been amazing. Each item exceeded our expectation and the food tasted incredibly fresh. I would definitely recommend this place for their fresh rolls, sushi, takoyaki, shumai, and mochi!
Always get take out from them. Very nice, never had a complaint. Very friendly service as well

I decided to give this restaurant a try considering I live 2 blocks away and it turned out to be quite a local gem. The restaurant inside is small ,cute and genuine. It is not decorated with corny nonsense like other sushi restaurants in South Brooklyn. It actually felt like I was in Japan when I set down. The sushi was great too ,the rice was perfect and fresh making the sushi melt in your mouth .The amount of fish that the chef puts into the sushi was a proper amount giving it a proper and full flavor. The service was on point as well. I am happy knowing that I have this wonderful little sushi spot right in my neighborhood.

I went to this resturant many years ago, last visit was in 2018? The portions are small and the price is very expensive. The price probably gone up by $2 to $4 by now, not going to support this japanese resturant since the portions are small and price is expensive.

Naniwa is AMAZING. I can not recommend their restaurant enough. I grew up in Bensonhurst eating with them and now that I’m in Midwood, they deliver to me in RECORD TIME. Yesterday, they delivered to me in under half an hour - JUST 26 MINUTES!!! Excellent service, always exceeding expectations. Never, ever, have waited more than an hour for delivery. And the food yesterday was just heavenly. Chef’s kiss. God bless this establishment!!!!

This place is right off the N train station. The interior is cute with some lovely art and they're able to accommodate a large group about 10 people.  The staffs are really sweet and kind.The prices are incredible compared to other sushi restaurants.  The appetizers are on the smaller size. For appetizers we got the kani salad, which is really good so we usually order like 2-3 of them. The rock shrimp was delicious too, served in a tall glass. Next we had the crab cakes and it was unexpectedly small but still very tasty! The edamame were great too- they add salt for better flavor.  For sushi, there's like 42 special rolls and some of my favorites are sex on the beach, tiffany roll, yummy roll, special kani roll, AK-47 roll. When you come here, skip the water and ask for the tea, it's one of the tastiest teas I've had, it's green tea with brown rice.

Why I gave this place a 1 star. This place has been here for awhile, and I've never went back after this incident (read on).  The last time I came here was late 2014 or early 2015. During the cold winter months. My friends ordered the typical california roll, sashimi order. I was still picking my order on the menu, when I noticed a bug on the table. It was a small cockroach. Needless to say, I didn't order dinner that night at that restaurant.  In my opinion: There's just so many sushi restaurants that if you are willing to travel a little further, it gets better. For instance, 86th street, bay parkway, avenue U. I believe competition in business builds quality. That way the customer would return to the better restaurant.

I wish I can give this place 0 starts, but I can't! I stopped going there a year ago because the fish is not fresh and the food is disgusting. I decided to give them a chance yesterday and went to eat. I ordered the simplest rolls and requested brown rice. It took them forty minutes to make what I requested, when I kept asking where it is they kept saying they are making the brown rice because they did not have it handy. As a restaurant, don't you think the right thing to do is gave a warning that this dish might take longer so that I can order an appetizer meanwhile? Obviously if I am coming there to eat, I am hungry. When the rolls finally came, it tasted like rubber. It was the most disgusting thing I ever tasted. The vegetables were not fresh and when we complained about it they did not even offer to make up for it. This is the worst customer service and food. PLEASE STAY FAR AWAY, you will do yourself a favor.
